 width.sh ACID test (quit: ctrl+w  scroll: arrows/pgup/pgdn)
  If widths are correct, all vertical borders align.
  +- CJK ideographs (width 2) ---------------------------------+
  | Chinese              | 中文                     | w=4      |
  | Japanese kanji       | 日本語                   | w=6      |
  | single CJK           | 漢                       | w=2      |
  | CJK + ASCII          | hi中文                   | w=6      |
  | interleaved          | 中a文b                   | w=6      |
  | CJK sentence         | 你好世界                 | w=8      |
  +----------------------+--------------------------+----------+
  +- Japanese kana (width 2) ----------------------------------+
  | Hiragana             | あいう                   | w=6      |
  | Katakana             | アイウ                   | w=6      |
  | mixed kana           | あアい                   | w=6      |
  +----------------------+--------------------------+----------+
  +- Korean (width 2) -----------------------------------------+
  | Hangul               | 한글                     | w=4      |
  | Korean word          | 가나다                   | w=6      |
  | Hangul + ASCII       | 한a글b                   | w=6      |
  +----------------------+--------------------------+----------+
  +- Fullwidth Latin (width 2) --------------------------------+
  | fullwidth A          | Ａ                       | w=2      |
  | fullwidth ABC        | ＡＢＣ                   | w=6      |
  | fw vs normal         | AＡ                      | w=3      |
